---
description: Required project structure, route layout, product data model, and i18n rules.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Project Structure

- Keep pages inside `app/` using route-based locale structure:
  - `app/[locale]/page.tsx`
  - `app/[locale]/products`
  - `app/[locale]/about`
  - `app/[locale]/contact`
  - product details at `app/[locale]/products/[slug]`
- Keep reusable UI in `components/ui`.
- Keep layout components in `components/layout` (for example Navbar and Footer).
- Keep page sections in `components/sections` (for example Hero and ProductGrid).
- Store static data in `data/*.json`.
- Do not hardcode large content in components.
- Do not change this structure unless explicitly requested.

# Product Data Rules

- Product display must be data-driven (JSON or CMS).
- Product records must include:
  - `name`
  - `description`
  - `image`
  - `slug`
- Reuse shared product card components for list/grid displays.

# Internationalization Rules

- Site must support multiple locales via `[locale]` routes (for example `/en`, `/vi`).
- Do not hardcode user-facing text in components.
- Store translations in:
  - `messages/en.json`
  - `messages/vi.json`
- Use translation lookup pattern like `t('key')`.
- Keep translation keys consistent and structured (for example `home.hero.title`, `products.list.title`).
